genresAdvancedInfo.name: oromo pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Oromo Pop - Oromo Pop is a genre of popular music that has emerged from the Oromo people of Ethiopia. The sound is characterized by its fusion of traditional Oromo music with modern pop and electronic elements. Oromo Pop artists often sing in the Oromo language and address themes of identity, social justice, and cultural preservation. The genre has gained popularity both within the Oromo community and beyond, and has been credited with helping to raise awareness of Oromo culture and history.
